asset.author: campchef
asset.hookText:
When I bought this stove years ago, it never entered my mind to do a review of it. I was looking for a sturdy, reliable propane double burner that would have a hard life, and that I could depend on. I would ask a lot: It would have to be sturdy enough to hold large cast iron Dutch ovens full of food, along with large containers of boiling water.
Despite my neglect, the stove has never let me down, and it has been used regularly, every week in my backyard when it isn't on camping trips.
I don't rep for Camp Chef, and I won't promote a product I wouldn't use myself.
